<section id="intro">
    <div class="d-flex flex-column justify-content-center align-items-center">
        <blockquote class="blockquote w-75" style="font-size: 1em; font-style: italic">
            <p class="quote">
                The PIXL (Planetary Instrument for X-ray Lithochemistry) for the Perseverance rover is a microfocus
                X-ray fluorescence instrument that rapidly measures elemental chemistry at sub-millimeter scales by
                focusing an X-ray beam to a tiny spot on the target rock or soil and analyzing the induced X-ray
                fluorescence.
            </p>
            <footer class="blockquote-footer">NASA Mars 2020</footer>
        </blockquote>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="project-desc">
    <h3>About The Project</h3>
    <div class="d-flex flex-direction-row">
        <img src="https://mars.nasa.gov/system/resources/detail_files/8223_nasa-mars-2020-rover-arm-extended_9k_still-1200.jpg"
            class="img-thumbnail mr-5" style="width: 350px">
        <div class="description">
            <p>
                Using the data obtained via the PiXL's sensitive X-Ray equipment, this project explores the spatial
                and chemical features of Mars' planetary composition.</p>
            <p>
                Built with a Node.js REST API backend that converts the raw data into an accessible JSON format,
                interactive visualization views of the data are achieved with the d3.js library.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>
